snippet: Election Day had its share of flaws and partisan disputes, but it was unclear whether any would cause a major shift in the result or set the stage for a big lawsuit.
abstract: Voting in many states is marred by long lines, demands for ID and a high number of provisional ballots, but so far no suits have been filed that could cause a major shift in election results.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Jon Hurdle from Philadelphia, Lizette Alvarez from Miami, Campbell Robertson from Tampa, Fla., Monica Davey from Cincinnati, Manny Fernandez from Houston, Michael Grynbaum from Milwaukee, Jack Healy from Denver, Fernanda Santos from Phoenix, Kim Severson from Atlanta and Julia Preston from New York.

lead_paragraph: Election Day had its share of flaws and partisan disputes, but it was unclear whether any would cause a major shift in the result or set the stage for a big lawsuit.
